The Federal Inland Revenue Service has issued a public notice on the establishment of its Large Taxpayers’ Office in Awka, Anambra State. A statement by the Service signed by its Executive Chairman, Mohammad Nami said the office is located at Plot 4, Abuja Estate, Glass House, Opp. Government House, Enugu/Onitsha Express Way, Awka, Anambra State. The announcement said the new office is in a bid to further improve ”our services, promote voluntary compliance and ease of paying taxes.” Find the announcement below…<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-820137" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/E0F3D4BB-6F36-42C4-82DF-1E0E7E5F9049.png" alt="" width="1242" height="2208" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/E0F3D4BB-6F36-42C4-82DF-1E0E7E5F9049.png 1242w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/E0F3D4BB-6F36-42C4-82DF-1E0E7E5F9049-169x300.png 169w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/E0F3D4BB-6F36-42C4-82DF-1E0E7E5F9049-576x1024.png 576w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/E0F3D4BB-6F36-42C4-82DF-1E0E7E5F9049-864x1536.png 864w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/E0F3D4BB-6F36-42C4-82DF-1E0E7E5F9049-1152x2048.png 1152w" sizes="(max-width: 1242px) 100vw, 1242px">